cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the problem of filtering noise from environmental audio recordings, specifically rain and cicada choruses, to improve the detection of bird sounds. The use of acoustic indices and machine learning classifiers to detect and filter these noise sources suggests a focus on signal processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly found in the sub-categories of cs.SD (Sound), cs.SI (Signal Processing), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of acoustic features and classifiers for detection suggests a focus on artificial intelligence and information retrieval, which are found in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
